    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rough place on a blown glass piece where the pontil rod has been broken away. May be ground or ground and polished to form a smooth circular depression.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000038561/Spillman, Glass Tableware (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ruwe plek op een geblazen glazen object waar de pontil rod weggebroken is. Kan worden geslepen of geslepen en gepolijst zodat een gladde ronde holte ontstaat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>吹製玻璃物件上的粗糙部分，為點棒（pontil rod）與玻璃製品脫離之處。可透過打磨或磨亮的方式，使圓形凹處變得平滑。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
